| return Statement in Java |
============================
👉 The return statement is used to terminate a method and send a value back to the caller.
   👉 Ends the execution of a method.
   👉 Returns a value to the caller (if the method is non-void).
   👉 In a void method, it can be used to exit the method without returning a value.
  👉  Statements after return are unreachable.

return value; -> Returning a Value
return a + b; -> Returning an Expression
int sum = a + b;
return sum;  -> Returning a Variable

---------------------------------------------------------- // Multiple Return Statements
public class Main {
    public static int max(int a, int b) {
        if (a > b) {
            return a;
        }
        return b;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(max(50, 30));
    }
}
---------------------------------------------------------- // return Inside if-else
public class Main {
    public static String check(int age) {
        if (age >= 18) {
            return "Adult";
        } else {
            return "Minor";
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(check(20));
    }
}

