Static vs Non-Static Difference
--------------------------------
____________________________________________________
| Static Method           | Non-Static Method      |
| ----------------------- | ---------------------- |
| Belongs to class        | Belongs to object      |
| Uses `static` keyword   | No `static` keyword    |
| Object not required     | Object required        |
| Called using class name | Called using object    |
| Memory once             | Each object has access |
| Faster                  | Slightly more overhead |
